Merge pull request #7 from ckuethe/repeat_modes

repeat mode for image source

repeat mode for image source

The difference between repeat modes is that mode 1 decodes the image
to a buffer and then continuously emits lines; mode 2 will re-open the
source file after emitting the last line allowing thus allowing the
the transmitted image to be changed by swapping out the file on disk
